President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Camila A. Alire and Ramón Saldívar for key administration posts. Camila A. Alire is a Dean Emerita at the University of New Mexico and Colorado State University, and has served as President of the American Library Association. Ramón Saldívar is the Hoagland Family Chair at Stanford University, specializing in Chicano and Chicana studies. Both nominees have extensive backgrounds in academia and have made significant contributions to their respective fields.